We pick nicknames.

197
00:17:07,793 --> 00:17:11,330
-Oh, yeah? What's it say?
-"Hot Rod."

198
00:17:14,299 --> 00:17:16,368
-Did you have a nickname?
-Yep.

199
00:17:16,502 --> 00:17:19,304
-What?
-"Ten-Gallon Head."

200
00:17:19,438 --> 00:17:22,408
-What's that?
-I grew up in Louisiana, near Texas.

201
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:27,279
Everybody wears cowboy hats.
And a ten-gallon's a big hat.

202
00:17:27,413 --> 00:17:31,083
I was smart back then,
so they called me Ten-Gallon Head.

203
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:33,685
-Hoss wears that hat.
-Hoss?

204
00:17:33,819 --> 00:17:35,687
Hoss Cartwright on Bonanza.

205
00:17:36,188 --> 00:17:39,658
-How do you know Bonanza?
-We watch it at Mrs. Chu's.

206
00:17:40,359 --> 00:17:43,462
-You watch Bonanza at daycare?
-Yeah.

207
00:17:44,496 --> 00:17:46,565
When? When do you watch it?

208
00:17:46,698 --> 00:17:50,469
-After snack? After your nap?
-After Love Boat.

209
00:17:55,374 --> 00:17:57,543
I made my list for my birthday.

210
00:17:58,310 --> 00:18:02,781
-Yeah, what'd you put on there?
-A basketball or an ant farm.

211
00:18:06,452 --> 00:18:10,689
-He says he's been watching TV.
-Oh, little TV for history.

212
00:18:10,823 --> 00:18:14,126
-Love Boat?
