236
00:20:20,852 --> 00:20:24,623
Yes. Beautiful. Beautiful.
Thank you, thank you.

237
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:37,369
Hey! Hey!

238
00:20:38,437 --> 00:20:39,738
Hey!

239
00:20:39,871 --> 00:20:41,406
This part of my life...

240
00:20:41,540 --> 00:20:44,343
-Wait!
-...this part here...

241
00:20:45,744 --> 00:20:47,479
...it's called "Running."

242
00:20:47,613 --> 00:20:49,615
Hey! Hey!

243
00:20:49,748 --> 00:20:51,416
Wait!

244
00:20:52,317 --> 00:20:55,020
Hey! Wait!

245
00:20:55,354 --> 00:20:57,656
That was my stolen machine.

246
00:20:57,789 --> 00:20:59,891
Unless she was with
a guy who sold them too.

247
00:21:01,493 --> 00:21:02,694
Which was unlikely...

248
00:21:02,828 --> 00:21:05,597
...because I was the only one
selling them in the Bay Area.

249
00:21:05,731 --> 00:21:08,500
I spent our entire life savings
on these things.

250
00:21:10,769 --> 00:21:14,506
It was such
a revolutionary machine.

251
00:21:15,574 --> 00:21:17,009
-Can you feel it, baby?
-Oh, yeah.

252
00:21:17,342 --> 00:21:18,744
You got me doing all the work.

253
00:21:18,877 --> 00:21:21,513
What I didn't know
is that doctors and hospitals...

254
00:21:21,647 --> 00:21:25,584
...would consider them
unnecessary luxuries.

255
00:21:28,053 --> 00:21:31,657
I even asked the landlord
to take a picture.

256
00:21:32,824 --> 00:21:37,796
So if I lost one, it was like losing
a month's groceries.

257
00:21:40,666 --> 00:21:43,669
Hey, hey! Wait! Wait!

258
00:21:46,538 --> 00:21:49,341
Hey, get back here!

259
00:21:53,779 --> 00:21:56,415
Hey, man, I--

260
00:21:58,050 --> 00:22:00,552
-Who's he?
-He's that guy....

261
00:22:10,896 --> 00:22:14,833
-Did you forget?
-Forget what?

262
00:22:15,767 --> 00:22:18,403
You're not supposed
to have any of those.

263
00:22:18,537 --> 00:22:21,740
-Yeah, I know.
-You have two now.

264
00:22:32,017 --> 00:22:33,685
Hey.

265
00:22:36,588 --> 00:22:38,123
Hey, Mom.

266
00:22:43,595 --> 00:22:47,499
One, two, three!

267
00:22:48,533 --> 00:22:51,670
-That's a basketball!
-Hey, hey. What do you mean?

268
00:22:51,803 --> 00:22:53,672
You don't know that
that's a basketball.

269
00:22:53,805 --> 00:22:57,709
This could be an ant farm. This could
be a microscope or anything.

270
00:22:57,843 --> 00:23:00,445
-No, it's not.
-There, there.

271
00:23:00,746 --> 00:23:03,849
All right, come on.
Open him up. Open him up.

272
00:23:09,688 --> 00:23:14,059
-That paper's a little heavy, huh?
-Yeah, but I got it.

273
00:23:25,403 --> 00:23:27,906
You should've seen me
out there today.

274
00:23:28,039 --> 00:23:30,776
Somebody stole a scanner.
I had to run the old girl down--

275
00:23:30,909 --> 00:23:32,511
Whatever.

276
00:23:33,945 --> 00:23:37,048
-What?
-Whatever, Chris.

277
00:23:37,682 --> 00:23:39,584
What the hell
you got attitude about?

278
00:23:39,718 --> 00:23:42,587
-"Whatever" what?
-Every day's got some damn story.

279
00:23:42,721 --> 00:23:44,022
Hey, Roy. Roy!

280
00:23:44,156 --> 00:23:46,658
Can you beat your little rug
when nobody's out here?

281
00:23:46,792 --> 00:23:48,160
There's dust and shit all over.

282
00:23:48,493 --> 00:23:50,896
-I'm trying to keep a clean house.
-Hey, wait a second.

283
00:23:51,029 --> 00:23:53,799
Listen. Look, Linda, relax.

284
00:23:53,932 --> 00:23:57,469
We're gonna come out of this.
Everything is gonna be fine, all right?

285
00:23:58,503 --> 00:24:02,440
You said that before,
when I got pregnant. "It'll be fine."

286
00:24:02,574 --> 00:24:07,612
-So you don't trust me now?
-Whatever. I don't care.

287
00:24:22,727 --> 00:24:24,963
-Taxi!
-Mr. Twistle.

288
00:24:25,096 --> 00:24:27,833
-Yeah, hi.
-Hi. Chris Gardner.

289
00:24:27,966 --> 00:24:29,835
Yeah, hi. Listen.
What can I do for you?

290
00:24:29,968 --> 00:24:33,138
I submitted an application for the
intern program about a month ago...

291
00:24:33,471 --> 00:24:35,707
...and I would just love
to sit with you briefly--

292
00:24:35,841 --> 00:24:37,776
Listen, I'm going
to Noe Valley, Chris.

293
00:24:37,909 --> 00:24:41,179
-Take care of yourself.
-Mr. Twistle.

294
00:24:41,513 --> 00:24:43,849
Actually, I'm on my way
to Noe Valley also.

295
00:24:43,982 --> 00:24:45,784
How about we share a ride?

296
00:24:47,152 --> 00:24:49,521
-All right, get in.
-All right.

297
00:24:55,594 --> 00:24:58,196
So when I was in the Navy,
I worked for a doctor...

298
00:24:58,530 --> 00:25:01,233
...who loved to play golf,
hours every day...

299
00:25:01,566 --> 00:25:06,104
...and I would actually
perform medical procedures...

300
00:25:06,238 --> 00:25:07,973
...when he'd leave me in the office.

301
00:25:08,106 --> 00:25:13,278
So I'm used to being in a position
where I have to make decisions and....

302
00:25:14,846 --> 00:25:17,749
Mr. Twistle, listen.
This is a very important--

303
00:25:17,883 --> 00:25:20,051
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
This thing's impossible.

304
00:25:22,087 --> 00:25:24,222
-I can do it.
-No, you can't. No one can.

305
00:25:24,556 --> 00:25:27,125
-That's bullshit.
-No, I'm pretty sure I can do it.

306
00:25:27,659 --> 00:25:30,829
-No, you can't.
-Let me see it.

307
00:25:31,263 --> 00:25:32,664
Give it here.

308
00:25:35,634 --> 00:25:39,905
Oh, yeah. Oh, wow,
you really messed it up.

309
00:25:40,038 --> 00:25:41,673
Sorry.

310
00:25:42,073 --> 00:25:48,079
It looks like it works around a swivel,
so the center pieces never move.

311
00:25:48,213 --> 00:25:51,316
So if it's yellow in the center,
that's the yellow side.

312
00:25:51,650 --> 00:25:54,085
If it's red in the center,
that's the red side.

313
00:25:54,219 --> 00:25:57,956
-Okay.
-So.... You can slow down.

314
00:25:58,089 --> 00:26:01,226
Listen, we can drive around all day.
I don't believe you can do this.

315
00:26:01,559 --> 00:26:03,061
-Yeah, I can.
-No, you can't.

316
00:26:03,194 --> 00:26:04,596
-Yes, I can.
-No, you can't.

317
00:26:04,729 --> 00:26:06,698
I'm telling you, no one can.

318
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:10,835
See? That's all I ever do.

319
00:26:23,715 --> 00:26:25,984
You almost have this side.

320
00:26:26,651 --> 00:26:28,053
Holy cow.

321
00:26:38,196 --> 00:26:42,067
-You almost had that one.
-I'm gonna get it.

322
00:26:49,674 --> 00:26:51,309
Look at that.

323
00:27:14,699 --> 00:27:15,900
You're almost there.

324
00:27:39,657 --> 00:27:43,261
-17.10.
-This is me.

325
00:27:45,330 --> 00:27:46,898
Good job.

326
00:27:48,700 --> 00:27:51,836
-Goodbye.
-Yeah. I'll see you soon.

327
00:27:54,139 --> 00:27:55,940
Where are you going, sir?

328
00:27:56,074 --> 00:27:59,110
Excuse me, sir.
Where are you going, please?

329
00:28:02,313 --> 00:28:04,182
Two-- A couple of blocks.

330
00:28:04,315 --> 00:28:07,852
-Just flip around.
-Okay.

331
00:28:49,761 --> 00:28:52,397
Hey! Stop it! Hey!

332
00:28:52,831 --> 00:28:54,365
-Where are you going? Come here!
-No!

333
00:28:54,499 --> 00:28:57,335
-No, no, no!
-You asshole, give me my money!

334
00:28:57,469 --> 00:28:59,037
-Give me my money.
-Please stop.

335
00:28:59,170 --> 00:29:01,172
-Please, please, please!
-Son of a bitch.

336
00:29:01,306 --> 00:29:03,975
Please! He should've paid you!

337
00:29:04,109 --> 00:29:05,777
-Come here!
-I'm sorry.

338
00:29:05,910 --> 00:29:07,512
-I'm so sorry.
-I'll kick your ass!

339
00:29:08,046 --> 00:29:11,249
-I'm sorry!
-Idiot.

340
00:29:22,026 --> 00:29:23,328
I'll get you!

341
00:29:23,461 --> 00:29:27,098
I'm going to kill you!
I'm going to kill you!

342
00:29:42,380 --> 00:29:44,482
Hey!

343
00:29:44,816 --> 00:29:47,552
Stop it, you son of a bitch!

344
00:29:47,952 --> 00:29:50,054
Stop him!

345
00:29:53,358 --> 00:29:56,027
Stop him!

346
00:30:01,166 --> 00:30:02,967
The doors are closing.

347
00:30:03,101 --> 00:30:06,004
Please stand clear of the doors.

348
00:30:13,912 --> 00:30:17,048
No! No! No!

349
00:30:19,584 --> 00:30:21,452
No!

350
00:30:44,542 --> 00:30:47,078
-Hello?
-Hey, yeah.

351
00:30:47,212 --> 00:30:48,980
Sorry I couldn't
make it home on time.

352
00:30:49,113 --> 00:30:53,351
-Chris, I missed my shift.
-Yeah, I know. I'm sorry about that.

353
00:30:53,484 --> 00:30:56,955
Look, I'm on my way right now.
Are you all right with Christopher?

354
00:30:57,088 --> 00:30:59,390
I'm leaving. Chris, I'm leaving.

355
00:30:59,524 --> 00:31:01,559
-What?
-Did you hear what I said?

356
00:31:02,427 --> 00:31:06,397
I have my things together,
and I'm taking our son...

357
00:31:06,531 --> 00:31:08,199
...and we're gonna leave now.

358
00:31:08,466 --> 00:31:10,001
I'm gonna put the phone down.

359
00:31:10,134 --> 00:31:13,605
-Linda, wait a minute. Hold it, hold--
-I'm going to leave. We are leaving.

360
00:31:18,877 --> 00:31:22,914
It was right then that I started
thinking about Thomas Jefferson...

361
00:31:24,148 --> 00:31:26,517
...the Declaration of Independence...

362
00:31:26,985 --> 00:31:32,991
...and the part about our right to life,
liberty and the pursuit of happiness.

363
00:31:33,124 --> 00:31:34,993
And I remember thinking:

364
00:31:35,126 --> 00:31:39,464
How did he know
to put the "pursuit" part in there?

365
00:31:39,597 --> 00:31:44,402
That maybe happiness is something
that we can only pursue.

366
00:31:44,535 --> 00:31:47,572
And maybe we can actually
never have it...

367
00:31:48,006 --> 00:31:49,574
...no matter what.

368
00:31:49,908 --> 00:31:51,509
How did he know that?

369
00:31:56,681 --> 00:31:59,550
Linda. Linda.

370
00:32:32,450 --> 00:32:34,252
-Hello?
-Chris.

371
00:32:34,385 --> 00:32:37,121
-Who is this?
-Jay Twistle.

372
00:32:37,956 --> 00:32:39,657
-Hey.
-Dean Witter.

373
00:32:39,991 --> 00:32:42,593
Yeah, of course. How are you?

374
00:32:42,727 --> 00:32:45,330
I'm fine. Listen, do you still
wanna come in and talk?

375
00:32:45,463 --> 00:32:46,597
Yes, sir. Absolutely.

376
00:32:46,731 --> 00:32:49,968
I'll tell you what. Come on by
day after tomorrow, in the morning.

377
00:32:50,101 --> 00:32:53,738
We're interviewing for the internships.
You got a pen and paper?

378
00:32:54,105 --> 00:32:55,573
Yes. Yes, I do.

379
00:32:58,509 --> 00:33:01,346
-Hold on one second.
-All right.

380
00:33:05,216 --> 00:33:07,352
Hello?

381
00:33:07,485 --> 00:33:09,754
-Chris?
-Go ahead. I have one.

382
00:33:10,088 --> 00:33:12,690
Write this number down so you can
call my secretary, Janice.

383
00:33:13,024 --> 00:33:15,093
-She can give you all the specifics.
-Yep.

384
00:33:15,226 --> 00:33:17,128
-Okay, 415.
-415.

385
00:33:17,261 --> 00:33:19,063
-864.
-864.

386
00:33:19,197 --> 00:33:21,232
-0256.
-0256.

387
00:33:21,366 --> 00:33:24,402
-Yeah, extension 4796.
-4796.

388
00:33:24,535 --> 00:33:28,773
-Right. Call her tomorrow.
-Yes, sir. 415-864-0256.

389
00:33:29,107 --> 00:33:30,375
-Okay, buddy.
-All right, yes.

390
00:33:30,508 --> 00:33:32,677
-Thank you very much.
-We'll see you soon.

391
00:33:33,478 --> 00:33:36,647
864-0256.

392
00:33:36,781 --> 00:33:40,151
4796. Janice.

393
00:33:43,154 --> 00:33:45,056
-Chris.
-Hey.

394
00:33:45,189 --> 00:33:47,392
Did you--? Have you seen
Linda and Christopher?

395
00:33:47,525 --> 00:33:49,527
-No. You catch the game last night?
-No, no.

396
00:33:49,660 --> 00:33:51,162
You didn't see that, 118, 1--?

397
00:33:51,295 --> 00:33:53,531
Excuse me, did Linda
and Christopher come in here?

398
00:33:53,664 --> 00:33:57,402
-No, I haven't seen them.
-119-120. Double overtime.

399
00:33:57,535 --> 00:33:59,670
Moons hits a three-pointer
at 17 seconds left.

400
00:33:59,804 --> 00:34:01,506
Wayne, Wayne, Wayne.

401
00:34:01,639 --> 00:34:03,775
Can't talk to you
about numbers right now.

402
00:34:04,108 --> 00:34:06,644
-What's your problem with numbers?
-864-2....

403
00:34:06,778 --> 00:34:08,746
-And you owe me money.
-Yeah.

404
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:10,715
You owe me $14.

405
00:34:11,049 --> 00:34:12,784
I'm gonna get that to you.

406
00:34:13,651 --> 00:34:16,254
I need my money.
I need my money.

407
00:34:17,288 --> 00:34:19,424
Fourteen's a number.

408
00:34:45,716 --> 00:34:49,153
Hey, don't you ever take my son
away from me again.

409
00:34:49,287 --> 00:34:50,555
-You hear me?
-Leave me alone!

410
00:34:50,688 --> 00:34:52,557
Don't take my son away
from me again.

411
00:34:52,690 --> 00:34:54,559
Do you understand
what I'm saying to you?

412
00:34:54,692 --> 00:34:58,162
Don't you walk away from me when
I'm talking to you. Do you hear me?

413
00:34:58,296 --> 00:34:59,730
-Do you wanna leave?
-Yeah.

414
00:34:59,864 --> 00:35:02,767
-You wanna leave?
-Yes, I want to leave!

415
00:35:04,135 --> 00:35:05,837
Get the hell out of here,
then, Linda.

416
00:35:06,170 --> 00:35:08,639
Get the hell out of here.
Christopher's staying with me.

417
00:35:08,773 --> 00:35:11,242
You're the one that dragged
us down. You hear me?

418
00:35:11,375 --> 00:35:14,479
-You are so weak.
-No. I am not happy anymore.

419
00:35:14,612 --> 00:35:17,348
-I'm just not happy!
-Then go get happy, Linda!

420
00:35:17,482 --> 00:35:18,783
Just go get happy.

421
00:35:19,383 --> 00:35:21,319
But Christopher's living with me.

422
00:35:21,452 --> 00:35:23,321
-Stop!
-Did you hear what I said?

423
00:35:23,521 --> 00:35:25,890
Christopher's living with me!

424
00:35:52,183 --> 00:35:55,153
Hey. Come on, let's go.

425
00:35:55,286 --> 00:35:57,588
-How you doing, Mrs. Chu?
-Hi.

426
00:36:01,292 --> 00:36:03,794
-Where's Mom?
-Look, just get your stuff.

427
00:36:03,928 --> 00:36:07,532
But she told me she was
coming to pick me up today.

428
00:36:07,665 --> 00:36:09,700
Yeah, I know.

429
00:36:10,801 --> 00:36:15,540
I talked to Mom earlier.
Everything's fine, okay?

430
00:36:20,845 --> 00:36:23,247
Where do I sleep tonight?

431
00:36:23,381 --> 00:36:25,516
Let me ask you something.
Are you happy?

432
00:36:25,650 --> 00:36:28,419
-Yeah.
-All right. Because I'm happy.

433
00:36:28,553 --> 00:36:31,956
And if you're happy and I'm happy,
then that's a good thing, right?

434
00:36:32,290 --> 00:36:33,724
-Yeah.
-All right.

435
00:36:33,858 --> 00:36:35,927
You're sleeping with me.

436
00:36:36,260 --> 00:36:40,831
You're staying at home,
where you belong, all right?

437
00:36:55,346 --> 00:36:56,914
Christopher.

438
00:37:14,532 --> 00:37:17,435
Hey, listen. I need the rent.

439
00:37:17,568 --> 00:37:18,936
I can't wait anymore.

440
00:37:19,270 --> 00:37:21,606
Yeah, I'm good for that, Charlie.
I'm gonna get it.

441
00:37:21,739 --> 00:37:24,809
Why don't you go two blocks over
at the Mission Inn motel?

442
00:37:24,942 --> 00:37:26,611
It's half what you pay here.

443
00:37:26,744 --> 00:37:30,314
Listen, Chris. I need you out
of here in the morning.

444
00:37:31,515 --> 00:37:33,751
The hell am I supposed
to be out of here tomorrow?

445
00:37:33,884 --> 00:37:35,253
I got painters coming in.

446
00:37:35,386 --> 00:37:37,655
-All right, look. I need more time.
-No.

447
00:37:37,788 --> 00:37:39,924
All right, I'll paint it myself.

448
00:37:40,258 --> 00:37:45,596
All right, but I just-- I gotta have some
more time-- I got my son up in here.

449
00:37:50,434 --> 00:37:55,339
All right. One week.
And you paint it.

450
00:38:47,024 --> 00:38:48,759
Chris Gardner?

451
00:38:49,393 --> 00:38:51,996
Yeah. What happened?

452
00:38:52,330 --> 00:38:56,067
-Payable to the City of San Francisco.
-Does it have to be the full amount?

453
00:38:56,400 --> 00:38:59,837
You gotta pay each parking ticket,
otherwise, you're staying.

454
00:38:59,970 --> 00:39:01,572
This is all I got.

455
00:39:06,911 --> 00:39:09,714
We verify at 9:30
tomorrow morning.

456
00:39:10,114 --> 00:39:13,351
-What?
-You gotta stay until this thing clears.

457
00:39:15,453 --> 00:39:16,954
No.

458
00:39:17,088 --> 00:39:18,956
No, I can't spend the night here.

459
00:39:19,090 --> 00:39:21,792
-I have to pick up my son.
-We verify at 9:30 tomorrow.

460
00:39:21,926 --> 00:39:26,597
Sir, I have a job interview at Dean
Witter at 10:15 tomorrow morning.

461
00:39:26,731 --> 00:39:28,599
-I cannot stay--
-9:30 tomorrow morning.

462
00:39:28,733 --> 00:39:31,001
What am I supposed to do
with my son?

463
00:39:31,135 --> 00:39:33,738
-Is there anyone else who can--?
-I take care of him.

464
00:39:33,871 --> 00:39:36,941
Maybe we can go and have
Social Services pick him up.

465
00:39:40,945 --> 00:39:44,749
All right.
Can I have my phone call, please?

466
00:39:47,852 --> 00:39:50,087
-Hello.
-Hey.

467
00:39:50,421 --> 00:39:52,022
What do you want?

468
00:39:53,124 --> 00:39:57,862
You gotta get Christopher
from daycare. I can't.

469
00:39:58,963 --> 00:40:02,733
Just keep him for the night and I'm--
And-- Just one night.

470
00:40:02,867 --> 00:40:04,935
What happened?

471
00:40:05,069 --> 00:40:08,672
I'll pick him up
from daycare tomorrow.

472
00:40:08,806 --> 00:40:10,641
I'm gonna go right--
You can just--

473
00:40:10,775 --> 00:40:13,043
You can drop him off
and I'll pick him up.

474
00:40:13,511 --> 00:40:16,881
-No.
-Come on, Linda.

475
00:40:17,014 --> 00:40:21,452
-Why you doing that?
-No, I wanna take him to the park.

476
00:40:21,786 --> 00:40:25,890
To Golden Gate
after daycare tomorrow.

