-I need that money now, not later.
-When I get it, you get it, Ralph.

957
01:16:48,904 --> 01:16:50,839
Now!

958
01:16:54,343 --> 01:16:56,678
Hey, what's happening, man?

959
01:16:56,812 --> 01:16:59,715
Wayne, I need to get
that $14 from you.

960
01:17:01,249 --> 01:17:03,151
I thought I didn't owe you that now.

961
01:17:03,285 --> 01:17:06,388
-What? Why?
-Why what?

962
01:17:06,722 --> 01:17:09,024
Why would you think
you don't owe me my money?

963
01:17:09,157 --> 01:17:11,159
I helped you move.

964
01:17:13,328 --> 01:17:16,264
You drove me two blocks, Wayne.

965
01:17:16,398 --> 01:17:18,266
That's 200 yards.

966
01:17:18,400 --> 01:17:20,369
It's been four months, Wayne.

967
01:17:20,702 --> 01:17:24,206
I need my money. I need my money.
I need my money right now.

968
01:17:24,339 --> 01:17:26,842
-I don't have it, man. I'm sorry.
-Go get my money.

969
01:17:26,975 --> 01:17:29,177
-Wayne, get my mo--
-I really don't, man. It's $14.

970
01:17:29,311 --> 01:17:31,113
It's my $14!
Go get my money!

971
01:17:31,246 --> 01:17:33,915
-All of this for $14.
-Get my money, Wayne.

972
01:17:52,167 --> 01:17:54,336
Dad, look at me!

973
01:17:54,870 --> 01:17:56,672
Dad.

974
01:17:57,439 --> 01:18:01,109
-Should I go?
-Sure, man. Why not?

975
01:18:17,125 --> 01:18:18,193
-Stay here.
-Dad, look.

976
01:18:18,326 --> 01:18:20,062
-No, no. Stay right here.
-Dad.

977
01:18:20,195 --> 01:18:23,031
Did you hear what I said?
Did you hear me?

978
01:18:28,070 --> 01:18:31,707
-Dad, where you going?
-Hey, what did I say?

979
01:18:34,710 --> 01:18:36,244
Dad!

980
01:18:36,378 --> 01:18:39,948
Dad, wait! Dad!

981
01:18:48,023 --> 01:18:50,092
-Dad.
-I gotta--

982
01:18:50,225 --> 01:18:53,762
I gotta get back to the '60s, man.
That's what I wanna do.

983
01:18:53,895 --> 01:18:58,166
When I was younger. I wanna see
Jimi Hendrix do that guitar on fire.

984
01:19:01,203 --> 01:19:03,972
Bring back my time machine!

985
01:19:05,240 --> 01:19:06,975
Bring my time machine back!

986
01:19:15,851 --> 01:19:19,387
-Dad, where are we going?
-Be quiet.

987
01:19:20,021 --> 01:19:22,858
Go get your things. Go.

988
01:19:45,981 --> 01:19:47,549
-Chris?
-Yes.

989
01:19:47,883 --> 01:19:51,853
Dr. Telm can't get back to meet you.
I'm sorry.

990
01:20:02,964 --> 01:20:05,367
Where are we going now?

991
01:20:06,134 --> 01:20:09,404
We gotta-- We gotta
see somebody else.

992
01:20:11,439 --> 01:20:13,575
I'm tired.

993
01:20:15,577 --> 01:20:17,312
I know.

994
01:20:24,586 --> 01:20:28,890
Doesn't seem to be functioning
right now.

995
01:20:29,191 --> 01:20:31,459
-I have to go now, Chris.
-No, no, no.

996
01:20:31,593 --> 01:20:35,530
Just give me a second. I'm sure
I'm gonna be able to figure it out.

997
01:20:37,332 --> 01:20:39,601
Chris. Chris, just come back
when it's working.

998
01:20:39,935 --> 01:20:42,838
-No, no. I have to fix it now.
-No.

999
01:20:42,971 --> 01:20:48,210
Look, I'll still be putting money
in the office, then, all right?

1000
01:20:48,343 --> 01:20:50,478
I really have to go, Chris.

1001
01:20:51,613 --> 01:20:53,381
Thank you. Thank you.

1002
01:20:53,515 --> 01:20:55,450
Thank you for your time.
I appreciate it.

1003
01:20:55,584 --> 01:20:57,352
I'll see you soon.

1004
01:21:49,337 --> 01:21:51,907
Why are our things here?

1005
01:21:52,674 --> 01:21:54,409
Dad.

1006
01:22:37,018 --> 01:22:39,621
-Let's go. Come on.
-Where?

1007
01:22:41,289 --> 01:22:43,591
-Just out of here.
-Why?

1008
01:22:43,725 --> 01:22:46,728
-We can't stay here tonight.
-Yes, we can. Open the door!

1009
01:22:47,062 --> 01:22:50,065
-Did you hear what I said? Let's go.
-Open the door!

1010
01:22:51,599 --> 01:22:55,537
Hey, did you hear what I said?
Stop it.

1011
01:22:55,670 --> 01:22:57,305
Stop it.

1012
01:23:01,443 --> 01:23:03,078
Come on.

1013
01:23:12,087 --> 01:23:13,521
Come on.

1014
01:23:30,505 --> 01:23:32,240
Wayne!

1015
01:23:33,274 --> 01:23:35,243
Wayne!

1016
01:23:42,350 --> 01:23:44,652
Wayne!

1017
01:24:00,235 --> 01:24:04,039
Get up. Stand up. Come on.

1018
01:24:19,687 --> 01:24:21,756
Where are we going?

1019
01:24:24,059 --> 01:24:27,362
-Dad, where are we going?
-I don't know.

1020
01:24:42,710 --> 01:24:45,280
It's not a time machine.

1021
01:24:45,413 --> 01:24:46,781
Dad.

1022
01:24:47,248 --> 01:24:48,550
It's not a time machine.

1023
01:24:48,683 --> 01:24:52,120
The guy said it was a time machine.
It's not a time machine. He was wrong.

1024
01:24:52,420 --> 01:24:54,756
-What guy?
-The guy. He was at the park.

1025
01:24:55,090 --> 01:24:56,858
He said it was a time machine.

1026
01:25:03,264 --> 01:25:04,499
Yes, it is.

1027
01:25:06,134 --> 01:25:07,802
No, it's not.

1028
01:25:09,771 --> 01:25:11,773
-It is.
-No, it's not.

1029
01:25:18,113 --> 01:25:22,584
All we gotta do is push
this black button right here.

1030
01:25:25,687 --> 01:25:26,855
Wanna push it?

1031
01:25:31,426 --> 01:25:33,194
Okay.

1032
01:25:34,629 --> 01:25:36,297
Come on.

1033
01:25:37,665 --> 01:25:39,400
Come on, man.

1034
01:25:44,906 --> 01:25:46,207
Right here.

1035
01:25:46,508 --> 01:25:48,209
Wait a minute.
Where you wanna go?

1036
01:25:48,443 --> 01:25:50,512
I don't know.
Some place from before.

1037
01:25:50,912 --> 01:25:52,313
You gotta close your eyes.

1038
01:25:52,514 --> 01:25:54,449
You close your eyes. I wanna see.

1039
01:25:56,551 --> 01:25:58,920
All right, come on.
We'll push it together.

1040
01:26:04,659 --> 01:26:06,628
You gotta close your eyes.
Close your eyes.

1041
01:26:07,362 --> 01:26:09,531
It takes a few seconds.

1042
01:26:11,833 --> 01:26:13,801
Oh, my goodness.

1043
01:26:13,935 --> 01:26:16,304
Open, open, open!

1044
01:26:19,574 --> 01:26:22,343
-What is it?
-Dinosaurs.

1045
01:26:22,477 --> 01:26:24,679
-Where?
-You don't see all these dinosaurs?

1046
01:26:25,947 --> 01:26:29,684
Look around.
Look at all these dinosaurs.

1047
01:26:31,452 --> 01:26:33,821
-Do you see them?
-Yeah.

1048
01:26:33,955 --> 01:26:35,490
Wait. Come on, come on.

1049
01:26:35,623 --> 01:26:36,925
-Wait, watch out.
-What is it?

1050
01:26:37,258 --> 01:26:39,327
Don't step in the fire.
We're cavemen.

1051
01:26:39,460 --> 01:26:41,763
We need this fire,
because there's no electricity...

1052
01:26:41,896 --> 01:26:43,498
...and it's cold out here, okay?

1053
01:26:44,232 --> 01:26:46,568
-Watch out!
-Whoa! Oh, my good-- A T. rex.

1054
01:26:46,701 --> 01:26:50,438
Get your stuff.
Get your stuff. Get it.

1055
01:26:51,372 --> 01:26:54,475
-We gotta find someplace safe.
-Like what?

1056
01:26:54,609 --> 01:26:56,611
We need a cave.

1057
01:26:56,744 --> 01:26:57,845
A cave?

1058
01:26:57,979 --> 01:27:00,248
-We gotta find a cave. Come on.
-Okay.

1059
01:27:00,381 --> 01:27:02,217
Come on, come on.

1060
01:27:03,651 --> 01:27:04,986
Watch your back! Look out.

1061
01:27:05,320 --> 01:27:07,388
Here it is. Here's a cave. Come on.

1062
01:27:07,522 --> 01:27:10,458
Right here, right here.
Go, go, go.

1063
01:27:10,592 --> 01:27:11,826
Go ahead. Get in.

1064
01:27:11,960 --> 01:27:13,861
Hurry, hurry, hurry.

1065
01:27:17,532 --> 01:27:21,369
-Are we safe?
-Yeah, I think so.

1066
01:28:29,337 --> 01:28:30,872
Hey.

1067
01:28:32,507 --> 01:28:34,075
-How you doing, Jay?
-I'm doing good.

1068
01:28:34,409 --> 01:28:35,777
How are you getting along?

1069
01:28:35,910 --> 01:28:38,079
-Good. I'm good.
-You doing good?

1070
01:28:38,413 --> 01:28:40,882
-How you doing?
-I'm doing great.

1071
01:28:41,949 --> 01:28:43,685
Where you going?

1072
01:28:46,888 --> 01:28:49,957
I-- Sacramento.

1073
01:28:50,658 --> 01:28:53,394
Because I'm trying to move
a couple guys from--

1074
01:28:53,528 --> 01:28:56,064
They're at PacBell,
and I'm trying to bring them over--

1075
01:28:56,397 --> 01:28:57,598
Get them over to us.

1076
01:28:57,732 --> 01:28:59,567
So they got me
going out there golfing.

1077
01:28:59,701 --> 01:29:01,602
Awesome.

1078
01:29:01,736 --> 01:29:03,738
Hey, let them win a round.

1079
01:29:08,843 --> 01:29:10,878
Deborah, someone's asking for you.

1080
01:29:11,012 --> 01:29:14,115
-Where?
-He's outside. Please come with me.

1081
01:29:21,989 --> 01:29:25,126
-Hi.
-How you doing?

1082
01:29:26,894 --> 01:29:29,564
-Can I ask you a question?
-Sure.

1083
01:29:31,733 --> 01:29:33,468
We need a room.

1084
01:29:33,901 --> 01:29:36,871
Just until I can fix this and sell it.

1085
01:29:37,004 --> 01:29:39,807
-There's just some glass work.
-Let me stop you right there.

1086
01:29:39,941 --> 01:29:42,610
-I wish I could help you--
-This is my son, Christopher.

1087
01:29:42,744 --> 01:29:44,779
-He's 5 years old.
-Hi, baby.

1088
01:29:44,912 --> 01:29:48,015
-We need some place to stay.
-Okay, and I would love to help you...

1089
01:29:48,149 --> 01:29:51,052
...but we don't take men here.
It's only women and children.

1090
01:29:51,385 --> 01:29:54,489
He can stay here, but you have
to find someplace else to go.

1091
01:29:54,622 --> 01:29:55,957
We gotta stay together.

1092
01:29:56,090 --> 01:29:57,525
We got-- We're--

1093
01:29:57,658 --> 01:29:59,627
-Okay, listen.
-You gotta have some place--

1094
01:29:59,761 --> 01:30:02,697
Try Glide Memorial.
The building books up at 5.

1095
01:30:02,830 --> 01:30:04,465
So you hurry up. There's a line.

1096
01:30:04,599 --> 01:30:07,935
-And where is it? Come on.
-Ellis and Jones.

1097
01:30:43,104 --> 01:30:48,843
Hey, everybody. We have
four spots left, and that's all.

1098
01:30:49,143 --> 01:30:52,079
-Man.
-Hey, come on, man.

1099
01:30:52,213 --> 01:30:53,614
-Come on.
-Come on, what?

1100
01:30:53,748 --> 01:30:55,449
-Hey, that's my spot.
-Back off.

1101
01:30:55,583 --> 01:30:57,952
Come on, don't do this to me.
Don't--

1102
01:31:00,188 --> 01:31:01,923
Dad!

1103
01:31:02,223 --> 01:31:04,525
Stop it! Break it up!
Break it up!

1104
01:31:04,659 --> 01:31:06,160
Stop! Stop!

1105
01:31:06,494 --> 01:31:08,763
Get out of line, both of you.
Both of you.

1106
01:31:08,896 --> 01:31:11,599
I was here first. They told me
that we had to be on time.

1107
01:31:11,833 --> 01:31:13,801
I got here on time. I was in line.

1108
01:31:13,935 --> 01:31:15,770
I came from work, I got my son.

1109
01:31:15,903 --> 01:31:18,573
I was here on time.
We were here on time!

1110
01:31:18,706 --> 01:31:20,208
He sliced in front of him in line.

1111
01:31:20,541 --> 01:31:22,810
-Who did?
-He did.

1112
01:31:22,977 --> 01:31:27,648
Come on, come on, Rodney.
Come on. Let's go. Get out of line.

1113
01:31:36,824 --> 01:31:38,860
That's it. No more.

1114
01:31:45,833 --> 01:31:48,836
-What's your favorite color?
-Green.

1115
01:31:48,970 --> 01:31:50,204
Green?

1116
01:31:50,538 --> 01:31:53,574
-What do you like that's green?
-Trees.

1117
01:31:53,708 --> 01:31:56,744
Trees. What else?

1118
01:31:56,878 --> 01:31:58,279
Holly.

1119
01:32:00,047 --> 01:32:04,051
-Holly. What's holly?
-The Christmas stuff.

1120
01:32:04,819 --> 01:32:06,854
Christmas stuff.

1121
01:32:07,655 --> 01:32:09,290
What's that?

1122
01:32:12,627 --> 01:32:15,596
I guess they want us to go to sleep.

1123
01:32:22,036 --> 01:32:27,041
Here you go. We gotta make sure
Captain America's warm in there.

1124
01:32:27,575 --> 01:32:29,176
Can he breathe?

1125
01:32:29,310 --> 01:32:31,779
-He's good?
-Yeah.

1126
01:32:32,079 --> 01:32:34,115
-I gotta go work on the scanner--
-Don't go.

1127
01:32:34,248 --> 01:32:37,652
No, no, no. I'm gonna be
right outside the door.

1128
01:32:37,785 --> 01:32:41,923
All right? I'm just gonna be right there.
I'll leave the door open a little bit.

1129
01:32:42,256 --> 01:32:45,059
And I'll be able to hear you
if you call me.

1130
01:32:45,192 --> 01:32:47,795
I wanna go home.

1131
01:32:49,830 --> 01:32:53,701
But that's why I gotta
work on the scanner.

1132
01:32:54,635 --> 01:32:56,270
All right?

1133
01:32:56,604 --> 01:32:58,572
I'm gonna go out there.

1134
01:32:58,706 --> 01:33:02,043
I'm gonna leave the door open.
I'll be right up the stairs.

1135
01:33:03,044 --> 01:33:04,912
I'll be able to hear you
if you call me.

1136
01:33:05,813 --> 01:33:07,949
-All right?
-All right.

1137
01:33:08,082 --> 01:33:10,584
You gotta trust me, okay?

1138
01:33:10,718 --> 01:33:12,787
You gotta trust me.

1139
01:33:13,654 --> 01:33:16,223
I trust you. I trust you.

1140
01:33:16,357 --> 01:33:17,925
I trust you.

1141
01:33:18,059 --> 01:33:21,095
-I can't hear you.
-I trust you. I trust you.

1142
01:33:24,899 --> 01:33:26,701
Give me a kiss.

1143
01:33:39,213 --> 01:33:42,216
-I'll just be a little while, okay?
-All right.

1144
01:33:42,750 --> 01:33:45,152
-I'll be right here.
-Okay.

1145
01:33:45,286 --> 01:33:47,688
-Can you still hear me?
-Yeah.

1146
01:33:47,822 --> 01:33:49,256
-Can you hear me?
-Yeah.

1147
01:33:49,390 --> 01:33:51,993
-Do you trust me?
-Yeah.

1148
01:34:39,173 --> 01:34:40,908
-Yeah.
-Like that?

1149
01:34:41,042 --> 01:34:44,812
-Yeah, put that....
-Then you go like that.

1150
01:34:44,945 --> 01:34:48,382
-Is that okay?
-I don't know. What do you think?

1151
01:34:48,716 --> 01:34:49,784
Good.

1152
01:34:51,052 --> 01:34:53,254
Let's go. Get your stuff.

1153
01:34:54,422 --> 01:34:57,425
-Dad, why don't you leave it?
-We can't.

1154
01:34:57,758 --> 01:34:59,894
We're gonna have
a different room later.

1155
01:35:00,027 --> 01:35:01,695
Go.

1156
01:35:06,934 --> 01:35:08,269
Hey, Chris.

1157
01:35:08,402 --> 01:35:11,906
-Hey, good morning, Mr. Frakesh.
-What's up?

1158
01:35:12,907 --> 01:35:13,941
Work trip.

1159
01:35:14,075 --> 01:35:16,310
Your wife, Martha, works at
PacBell also, correct?

1160
01:35:16,444 --> 01:35:18,312
-Yes, she does.
-And you guys are both...

1161
01:35:18,446 --> 01:35:20,281
...looking to retire at the same time?

1162
01:35:20,414 --> 01:35:22,817
We'd like to retire
and maintain our lifestyle...

1163
01:35:22,950 --> 01:35:24,385
...without paying a lot of taxes.

1164
01:35:24,718 --> 01:35:28,022
So basically, you want nobody's hands
in your pockets but your own?

1165
01:35:28,422 --> 01:35:30,424
Are you familiar with
tax-free municipal...?

1166
01:35:30,758 --> 01:35:32,460
I learned to finish my work quickly.

1167
01:35:32,927 --> 01:35:35,096
I had to finish quickly.

1168
01:35:35,362 --> 01:35:38,966
To get in line at Glide by 5.

1169
01:35:42,503 --> 01:35:44,505
Come on.

1170
01:35:45,039 --> 01:35:46,740
Come on.

1171
01:35:50,778 --> 01:35:53,447
Hold that bus! Hold the bus!

1172
01:35:54,315 --> 01:35:56,183
My Captain America!

1173
01:35:56,317 --> 01:35:58,786
Dad! Dad! Dad!

1174
01:35:58,919 --> 01:36:02,156
Stop it! Shut up! Shut up!

1175
01:36:04,391 --> 01:36:06,460
-Why don't you let the lady in?
-Hey, back up.

1176
01:36:06,794 --> 01:36:09,864
-Hey, man, that's not cool.
-Back up! Back up!

1177
01:36:18,105 --> 01:36:19,507
Come on.

1178
01:36:22,476 --> 01:36:24,879
Dad, we need to get it!

1179
01:36:27,348 --> 01:36:30,084
The important thing about
that freedom train...

1180
01:36:30,217 --> 01:36:32,386
...is it's got to climb mountains.

1181
01:36:32,520 --> 01:36:35,356
We all have to deal with mountains.

1182
01:36:35,489 --> 01:36:38,459
You know, mountains
that go way up high.

1183
01:36:38,959 --> 01:36:41,028
And mountains that go
deep and low.

1184
01:36:41,162 --> 01:36:42,396
-Amen, preacher!
-Yes.

1185
01:36:42,530 --> 01:36:44,999
We know what those mountains are,
here at Glide.

1186
01:36:45,199 --> 01:36:47,334
We sing about them.

1187
01:36:48,135 --> 01:36:53,574
Lord, don't move that mountain

1188
01:36:55,075 --> 01:37:01,448
Give me strength to climb it

1189
01:37:02,049 --> 01:37:08,589
Please don't move
That stumbling block

1190
01:37:08,923 --> 01:37:15,429
But lead me, Lord, around it

1191
01:37:17,097 --> 01:37:22,169
My burdens, they get so heavy

1192
01:37:24,004 --> 01:37:29,543
Seems hard to bear

1193
01:37:30,477 --> 01:37:34,148
But I won't give up
No, no

1194
01:37:34,281 --> 01:37:36,350
Because you promised me

1195
01:37:36,483 --> 01:37:43,290
You'd meet me at the altar of prayer

1196
01:37:43,424 --> 01:37:51,098
-Lord don't move that mountain
-Please don't move that mountain

1197
01:37:51,232 --> 01:37:56,470
But give me strength to climb it

1198
01:37:58,639 --> 01:38:00,641
When's your test?

1199
01:38:01,976 --> 01:38:03,410
Tomorrow.

1200
01:38:07,881 --> 01:38:09,550
Are you ready?

1201
01:38:13,454 --> 01:38:15,022
Of course.

1202
01:38:54,094 --> 01:38:55,362
Thank you, sir.

1203
01:39:04,638 --> 01:39:07,041
-Hey. How you doing?
-Hey.

1204
01:39:11,011 --> 01:39:14,048
So did you finish the whole thing,
or you have to go somewhere...?

1205
01:39:14,181 --> 01:39:16,583
I have to go somewhere.

1206
01:39:17,184 --> 01:39:20,087
-But I finished the whole thing too.
-Oh, good.

1207
01:39:20,220 --> 01:39:22,189
-You?
-Yeah.

1208
01:39:22,589 --> 01:39:25,592
-How'd you feel about the graphs?
-Easy.

1209
01:39:26,560 --> 01:39:30,631
I struggled with the essay question
on the back. What did you write?

1210
01:39:30,964 --> 01:39:34,501
-Essay question?
-Yeah, on the back.

1211
01:39:44,411 --> 01:39:45,746
Hey, Chris.

1212
01:39:46,080 --> 01:39:49,316
-Hey. Jeff, right? 49ers game.
-Yeah.

1213
01:39:49,450 --> 01:39:53,087
-Yeah, you were gonna give me a call?
-I never actually got your number.

1214
01:39:54,021 --> 01:39:56,623
Listen. Here's my number.
Call me, okay?

1215
01:39:56,757 --> 01:39:59,526
Yes, sir. Absolutely.
Thank you very much.

1216
01:40:00,327 --> 01:40:04,164
Chris, you got five bucks?
I left my wallet upstairs.

1217
01:40:04,298 --> 01:40:06,533
Let me run up and grab that
for you, Mr. Frohm.

1218
01:40:06,667 --> 01:40:09,703
No, I gotta be at CAL Bank at 4,
and I'm late.

1219
01:40:15,175 --> 01:40:17,344
-I'll pay you back, honest.
-Five is good?

1220
01:40:17,478 --> 01:40:21,215
Five is lovely. Thank you.
Thank you.

1221
01:40:34,461 --> 01:40:37,097
That's it. That's the room quota.

1222
01:40:37,364 --> 01:40:40,200
There's no more space.
You gotta head out.

1223
01:40:40,334 --> 01:40:43,270
That's it for today.
Come back tomorrow.

1224
01:40:43,404 --> 01:40:46,440
All the rooms are full.
It's completely full.

1225
01:40:46,573 --> 01:40:51,044
That's it. Just keep heading out.
Come back tomorrow.

1226
01:41:25,813 --> 01:41:27,648
You like it?

1227
01:42:18,665 --> 01:42:22,436
Twenty. One, two, three, four.

1228
01:42:25,506 --> 01:42:29,209
Now, here's your bulb,
and there's your ferrite core inductor.

1229
01:42:29,343 --> 01:42:32,212
-How much?
-Eight dollars.

1230
01:42:33,247 --> 01:42:36,550
-What's that?
-It's to repair the light.

1231
01:42:36,683 --> 01:42:38,752
Can I see it?

1232
01:42:40,654 --> 01:42:43,724
Yeah, sure. Just don't break it.

1233
01:42:43,857 --> 01:42:48,495
Unless you wanna sleep in a room
with me for the rest of your life.

1234
01:42:49,630 --> 01:42:51,532
I don't mind.

1235
01:42:51,899 --> 01:42:53,800
Yeah, you will.

1236
01:43:10,183 --> 01:43:12,519
Why don't you
get some sleep, okay?

1237
01:43:12,653 --> 01:43:13,820
Okay.

1238
01:43:13,954 --> 01:43:17,257
-Warm enough?
-Yeah.

1239
01:43:17,424 --> 01:43:19,192
All right.

1240
01:43:21,261 --> 01:43:24,197
Did Mom leave because of me?

1241
01:43:27,434 --> 01:43:31,638
-What?
-Did Mom leave because of me?

1242
01:43:36,276 --> 01:43:40,714
Don't-- Don't even think
something like that.

1243
01:43:41,748 --> 01:43:43,884
Mom left because of Mom.

1244
01:43:44,217 --> 01:43:46,486
And you didn't have anything
to do with that, okay?

1245
01:43:46,987 --> 01:43:48,956
Okay.

1246
01:43:58,799 --> 01:44:00,867
You're a good papa.

1247
01:44:08,742 --> 01:44:10,744
All right, go to sleep.

1248
01:44:11,578 --> 01:44:14,548
-I love you.
-I love you too.

1249
01:45:10,904 --> 01:45:12,939
So far, so good, Chris.

1250
01:45:18,945 --> 01:45:21,648
-It works.
-Thank you very much.

1251
01:45:21,782 --> 01:45:25,686
Two hundred and fifty dollars.
Four more weeks of oxygen.

1252
01:45:25,919 --> 01:45:30,323
One hundred, 20, 40, 60, 80, 200.

1253
01:45:30,457 --> 01:45:33,093
Twenty, 30, 40, 50.

1254
01:45:34,394 --> 01:45:35,929
-Anything else?
-Nope, that's it.

1255
01:45:36,063 --> 01:45:37,564
Thank you. Thank you.

1256
01:45:37,698 --> 01:45:39,666
-You ready?
-Yep.

1257
01:45:41,568 --> 01:45:44,538
-Are we going to the church place?
-No.

1258
01:45:44,671 --> 01:45:46,673
Where are we going, then?

1259
01:45:47,474 --> 01:45:49,976
-Probably stay at a hotel.
-A hotel?

1260
01:45:50,110 --> 01:45:51,378
Just for the night.

1261
01:45:51,511 --> 01:45:54,347
We can go back to the cave
if you like.

1262
01:45:54,481 --> 01:45:56,116
No, thank you.

1263
01:45:56,450 --> 01:45:58,885
-Ever?
-I hope not.

1264
01:45:59,019 --> 01:46:00,587
Why not?

1265
01:46:00,721 --> 01:46:03,623
Well, because some things are fun
the first time you do them...

1266
01:46:03,757 --> 01:46:06,059
...and then not so much the next.

1267
01:46:06,393 --> 01:46:09,362
-Like the bus?
-Yeah, like the bus.

1268
01:46:09,496 --> 01:46:12,766
I'm sorry. Guess I shouldn't laugh,
should I?

1269
01:46:12,899 --> 01:46:16,470
It's promised in the Bible.
Pa says we'll find it some day.

1270
01:46:16,603 --> 01:46:18,805
He doesn't know where it is, though.

1271
01:46:19,873 --> 01:46:23,110
Didn't you ever want to have a home
of your own like other people?

1272
01:46:23,443 --> 01:46:25,011
Sure.

1273
01:46:25,612 --> 01:46:27,614
Sometimes when we're moving
at night...

1274
01:46:27,748 --> 01:46:30,851
...we pass houses with lights
and people.

1275
01:46:30,984 --> 01:46:33,754
Sometimes you can
hear them laughing....

1276
01:46:38,391 --> 01:46:41,728
The next day, after work...

1277
01:46:41,862 --> 01:46:44,064
...we just went to the beach.

1278
01:46:44,397 --> 01:46:46,166
Far away from anything.

1279
01:46:46,500 --> 01:46:47,801
Everything.

1280
01:46:47,934 --> 01:46:49,703
Just Christopher and me.

1281
01:46:51,171 --> 01:46:53,707
-Did you see me?
-Yeah.

1282
01:46:53,840 --> 01:46:56,943
Far away from buses and noise...

1283
01:46:57,077 --> 01:47:02,816
...and a constant disappointment
in my ten-gallon head...

1284
01:47:03,917 --> 01:47:05,852
...and in myself.

1285
01:47:06,520 --> 01:47:08,822
-Chris, thank you very much.
-Well, thank you, Dean.

1286
01:47:08,955 --> 01:47:10,891
-Take care.
-You made all the right moves.

1287
01:47:11,024 --> 01:47:12,659
Thanks, Chris.

1288
01:47:14,661 --> 01:47:15,962
Because when I was young...

1289
01:47:16,096 --> 01:47:19,933
...and I'd get an A on a history test
or whatever...

1290
01:47:20,066 --> 01:47:24,805
...I'd get this good feeling about
all the things that I could be.

1291
01:47:26,673 --> 01:47:30,210
And then I never became
any of them.

1292
01:47:37,818 --> 01:47:40,453
-Hey, Chris.
-Hey.

1293
01:47:40,587 --> 01:47:43,123
-How you doing, Jay?
-I'm doing fine.

1294
01:47:43,456 --> 01:47:47,594
Rumor has it you signed 31 accounts
for us from Pacific Bell.

1295
01:47:47,727 --> 01:47:49,095
Yeah, yeah.

1296
01:47:49,229 --> 01:47:53,099
Met some guys at a ball game,
got some cards. I've been working.

1297
01:47:53,233 --> 01:47:54,968
I guess.

1298
01:47:57,938 --> 01:48:00,140
So one more day.

1299
01:48:00,473 --> 01:48:01,975
Getting nervous?

1300
01:48:02,609 --> 01:48:04,945
-No, I'm okay.
-Yeah?

1301
01:48:05,078 --> 01:48:07,047
Listen, whatever happens...

1302
01:48:07,180 --> 01:48:09,749
...you've done a fantastic job, Chris.

1303
01:48:09,883 --> 01:48:11,585
I mean that.

1304
01:48:12,219 --> 01:48:14,120
Take care of yourself.

1305
01:48:29,035 --> 01:48:32,272
Yes, Mr. Johnson.
Chris Gardner, Dean Witter.

1306
01:48:32,606 --> 01:48:34,774
Yes, sir. Just calling
to thank you very much...

1307
01:48:34,908 --> 01:48:37,544
...for your support
at last month's seminar.

1308
01:48:37,944 --> 01:48:39,713
Yes, sir. Absolutely.

1309
01:48:40,180 --> 01:48:41,915
Yes, sir.

1310
01:48:42,048 --> 01:48:43,583
No, sir, that's it.

1311
01:48:43,717 --> 01:48:46,152
Thank you very much. Bye-bye.

1312
01:48:47,787 --> 01:48:50,724
Chris. Come.

1313
01:49:18,018 --> 01:49:21,121
-Hi, Chris.
-Mr. Frohm, good to see you.

1314
01:49:22,188 --> 01:49:24,190
-Nice shirt.
-Thank you, sir.

1315
01:49:24,324 --> 01:49:25,692
-Chris.
-Hey, Jay.

1316
01:49:26,026 --> 01:49:30,263
-Chris.
-Chris, sit down, please.

1317
01:49:33,199 --> 01:49:37,270
I thought I'd wear a shirt today.

1318
01:49:37,604 --> 01:49:39,606
You know,
being the last day and all.

1319
01:49:39,739 --> 01:49:43,043
Well, thank you. Thank you.
We appreciate that.

1320
01:49:43,944 --> 01:49:45,779
But...

1321
01:49:45,912 --> 01:49:48,782
...wear one tomorrow though, okay?

1322
01:49:48,915 --> 01:49:51,885
Because tomorrow's
going to be your first day...

1323
01:49:52,652 --> 01:49:55,855
...if you'd like to work here
as a broker.

1324
01:49:57,090 --> 01:49:58,992
Would you like that, Chris?

1325
01:49:59,893 --> 01:50:01,594
Yes, sir.

1326
01:50:01,728 --> 01:50:05,065
Good. We couldn't be happier.

1327
01:50:06,032 --> 01:50:09,169
So welcome.

1328
01:50:11,037 --> 01:50:16,076
-Was it as easy as it looked?
-No, sir. No, sir, it wasn't.

1329
01:50:18,311 --> 01:50:20,847
-Good luck, Chris.
-Thank you. Thank you.

1330
01:50:25,051 --> 01:50:26,753
Thank you, sir.

1331
01:50:27,153 --> 01:50:29,089
Oh, Chris.

1332
01:50:31,658 --> 01:50:33,760
I almost forgot.

1333
01:50:35,762 --> 01:50:37,263
Thank you.

1334
01:50:57,751 --> 01:50:59,919
This part of my life...

1335
01:51:00,820 --> 01:51:03,023
...this little part...

1336
01:51:06,259 --> 01:51:08,995
...is called "Happiness."

1337
01:51:55,742 --> 01:51:59,279
Christopher. Christopher.
Come here.

1338
01:52:29,142 --> 01:52:31,344
So how many...

1339
01:52:31,478 --> 01:52:33,446
...planets are there?

1340
01:52:34,848 --> 01:52:36,516
-Seven.
-Seven?

1341
01:52:37,117 --> 01:52:38,985
Nine.

1342
01:52:41,254 --> 01:52:43,356
Who's the king of the jungle?

1343
01:52:43,857 --> 01:52:46,459
-Gorilla.
-The gorilla?

1344
01:52:46,860 --> 01:52:48,228
The gorilla?

1345
01:52:48,361 --> 01:52:50,130
No. Lion.

1346
01:52:50,263 --> 01:52:52,966
Oh, yeah. Lion, lion, lion.

1347
01:52:55,001 --> 01:52:58,004
Hey, Dad, listen to this.
Knock, knock.

1348
01:52:58,138 --> 01:53:00,140
-Who's there?
-Shelby.

1349
01:53:00,273 --> 01:53:01,374
Shelby who?

1350
01:53:01,508 --> 01:53:05,378
Shelby coming around the mountain
When she comes

1351
01:53:06,212 --> 01:53:07,547
-Knock knock.
-Who's there?

1352
01:53:07,881 --> 01:53:10,283
-Nobody.
-Nobody who?

1353
01:53:11,151 --> 01:53:13,019
Nobody who?

1354
01:53:16,222 --> 01:53:19,225
Now, that's funny. I like that one.
